25/04/2010
BUCHAREST, Romania -- A prosecutor, two lawyers and two police officers were detained on Friday (April 23rd) for corruption. 
Nelu Carpen, head of the prosecution office in the town of Buftea, is accused of taking bribes from defendants to guarantee them favourable outcomes, with the help of the lawyers and police officers. 
Carpen was suspended from his duties Friday. 
(Romanian Times, Mediafax, Agerpres - 23/04/10)
